# Lester New Blog - Architecture Plan

## Scope
Implement issues #31-#44 as incremental milestones for an Astro-based blog with typed content collections, tag pages, SEO metadata, RSS/sitemap, and containerized deployment.

## Module Structure and File Organization

- `astro.config.mjs`
  - Astro integration config (Tailwind, sitemap integration, site URL, markdown settings)
- `tailwind.config.cjs`, `postcss.config.cjs`
  - Tailwind theme extensions and typography plugin config
- `tsconfig.json`
  - TypeScript strictness and path aliases
- `src/layouts/`
  - `BaseLayout.astro`: global page shell, nav/footer, base metadata wiring
- `src/components/`
  - `HeadSEO.astro`: canonical/meta/open-graph/twitter tags
  - `PostCard.astro`: reusable post preview for list pages
  - `TagBadge.astro`: tag rendering with links
- `src/content/`
  - `config.ts`: content collection schema (`blog`)
  - `blog/*.md`: markdown posts with frontmatter
- `src/pages/`
  - `index.astro`: home page post listing
  - `about.astro`: static about page
  - `tags/index.astro`: tag index and counts
  - `tags/[tag].astro`: individual tag page
  - `posts/[slug].astro`: dynamic blog post route
  - `rss.xml.ts`: RSS feed endpoint
- `src/styles/`
  - `global.css`: Tailwind base/components/utilities + typography tuning
- `src/lib/`
  - `content.ts`: helpers for sorted posts, filtering drafts, tag aggregation
  - `types.ts`: shared frontmatter/tag/meta types if needed
- `public/`
  - static assets (favicon, OG fallback image, etc.)
- Deployment
  - `Dockerfile`
  - `fly.toml`

## Shared Types and Contracts

- Blog frontmatter contract via Astro Content Collections schema:
  - `title: string`
  - `description: string`
  - `pubDate: Date`
  - `updatedDate?: Date`
  - `tags: string[]`
  - `draft?: boolean`
  - `heroImage?: string`
- Derived app-level contracts:
  - Normalized post shape from collection entries (for list/detail rendering)
  - Tag index map: `Record<string, number>` or `Map<string, number>`

## Dependencies Between Issues

1. #31 Initialize Astro + TS + Tailwind
   - Foundation for all remaining issues.
2. #32 Directory structure + base layout
   - Needed before implementing pages/components.
3. #33 Content Collections config
   - Required for post listing and dynamic post pages.
4. #34 Home page listing
   - Depends on #32 and #33.
5. #35 Dynamic post pages
   - Depends on #33; reuses base layout from #32.
6. #36 Tag index page
   - Depends on #33 and helper utilities.
7. #37 Individual tag pages
   - Depends on #33 and #36 data strategy.
8. #38 SEO/OG component
   - Cross-cutting; integrate into #34/#35/#41 pages and base layout.
9. #39 RSS generation
   - Depends on #33 and site metadata.
10. #40 Sitemap generation
   - Depends on #31 config and final route structure.
11. #41 About page
   - Depends on #32 layout and #38 SEO.
12. #42 Typography + responsive polish
   - Best after core pages exist.
13. #43 Dockerfile + Fly.io config
   - Depends on finalized build command/output.
14. #44 Sample content + final README
   - Final documentation and demo content after routes/components stabilize.

## Key Design Decisions

- Use Astro Content Collections as the single source of truth for content validation and typing.
- Keep listing/filtering logic in `src/lib/content.ts` to avoid duplication across home/tags/RSS.
- Normalize tags to URL-safe slugs for consistent tag routing.
- Centralize SEO in `HeadSEO.astro` to keep metadata consistent and avoid per-page drift.
- Prefer static generation for all pages (including posts/tags) for performance and deployment simplicity.
- Enable sitemap integration and RSS endpoint to satisfy discoverability with minimal custom infra.
- Use Tailwind + typography plugin for controlled, consistent markdown rendering and responsive rhythm.
- Containerize with multistage Docker build to keep image size small and runtime deterministic.
